<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">981</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1000</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19605652/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19605652</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.294095020">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=EBV+%3D+Epstein-Barr+virus&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">EBV = Epstein-Barr virus</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FDG+%3D+2-%5Bfluorine-18%5Dfluoro-2-deoxy-d-glucose&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FDG = 2-[fluorine-18]fluoro-2-deoxy-<span data-style="small-caps">d</span>-glucose</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PTLD+%3D+posttransplantation+lymphoproliferative+disorder&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PTLD = posttransplantation lymphoproliferative disorder</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The pathogenesis, classification, risk factors, distribution, clinical aspects, and imaging features of posttransplantation lymphoproliferative disorder are discussed and illustrated.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Amir A.</span> <span property="familyName">Borhani</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Diagnostic Imaging (A.A.B., K.H., O.A., A.F.) and Pathology (M.N.), University of Pittsburgh Medical Center (Presbyterian Campus), 200 Lothrop St, CHP MT Suite 3850, Pittsburgh, PA 15213. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received January 29, 2009; revision requested February 19 and received March 13; accepted March 16. M.N. is a consultant with CeloNova BioSciences; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Borhani/Amir+A" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Keyanoosh</span> <span property="familyName">Hosseinzadeh</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Diagnostic Imaging (A.A.B., K.H., O.A., A.F.) and Pathology (M.N.), University of Pittsburgh Medical Center (Presbyterian Campus), 200 Lothrop St, CHP MT Suite 3850, Pittsburgh, PA 15213. Presented 